// v1.3 forward (v2-updated): strict mode flags a spread whose
// source's static type is genuinely unknown. (The previous fixture
// used `1 + 2` as the source — v2 now flags that case cross-mode
// via `NonSpreadableSource`. An untyped closure parameter is the
// canonical "type genuinely unknown" case: `n` leaks `Any` so the
// inner spread has no derivable shape, and strict demands a hint.)
// EXPECTED: 1 × SpreadSourceTypeUnknown (plus the closure-param
// diagnostics for the untyped `n`).
#strict
{ f: (n) => { ...n } }
